Description: Stores all client information (name, contact, company details). The central hub for linking to devices, tickets, services, and plans.
Registers computers, laptops, or equipment linked to a customer. Tracks specifications, status, and service history.
Registers  services (repairs, maintenance, upgrades). related to customers and also to the devices (which are also related to the customer)
Manages spare parts inventory (screens, batteries, SSDs, etc.) and associates them with services when replacements are needed.
Tracks computers for sale (new and reconditioned units). Helps manage computers sales pipeline and stock.
Stores information of quotations and/or warranties about custom PC builds or gaming setups , this is because this kind of computer have different serial in each spare part.
Registers devices purchased from clients (for refurbishing or resale). Keeps acquisition cost and refurbishment details.
Generates and manages service or product quotes for customers. Can include services, parts, or devices from inventory.
Holds information about IT service plans, warranties, or maintenance contracts offered to customers.
Tracks business customer services requests/issues. Links to customers, devices, services, and plans. Core app for day-to-day support.
Manages scheduled visits, repairs, or customer meetings. Syncs with tickets or sales processes.
Registers individuals enrolled in Kupper’s training programs for technicians.
Catalog of training programs (e.g., hardware repair, networking, gaming PC assembly).
Specific sessions for a course (date, time, instructor, enrolled students).
Connects students to courses/classes. Tracks payments, attendance, and progress.
Divides courses into structured learning units (modules or topics) for curriculum management.
Saves technician whatsapp and related services
